WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:17.985 align:middle line:90%


00:00:17.985 --> 00:00:21.788 align:middle line:84%
Hi, I'm Lisa Garr, host
of "Gaiam Inspirations."

00:00:21.788 --> 00:00:24.057 align:middle line:10%
Did you know that
22% of the healing

00:00:24.057 --> 00:00:26.560 align:middle line:10%
of all breast cancer
cases is attributed

00:00:26.560 --> 00:00:28.562 align:middle line:10%
to spontaneous remissions?

00:00:28.562 --> 00:00:30.297 align:middle line:10%
Did you know that there's
a way to scientifically

00:00:30.297 --> 00:00:34.868 align:middle line:10%
validate healing hands using a
specific type of photography?

00:00:34.868 --> 00:00:37.571 align:middle line:10%
Did you know that you can
learn to do this yourself?

00:00:37.571 --> 00:00:39.539 align:middle line:84%
Well, joining me today
to help us explore

00:00:39.539 --> 00:00:42.676 align:middle line:84%
the power of reconnected
healing is internationally

00:00:42.676 --> 00:00:45.045 align:middle line:90%
recognized healer, Eric Pearl.

00:00:45.045 --> 00:00:46.980 align:middle line:84%
Not only has Eric spoken
by invitation at the United

00:00:46.980 --> 00:00:50.384 align:middle line:84%
Nations, he's presented to a
full house at Madison Square

00:00:50.384 --> 00:00:53.020 align:middle line:84%
Garden, he's been interviewed
in various publications,

00:00:53.020 --> 00:00:54.821 align:middle line:90%
including "The New York Times."

00:00:54.821 --> 00:00:58.525 align:middle line:84%
But he experienced an overnight
shift in his healing abilities

00:00:58.525 --> 00:01:00.928 align:middle line:90%
he calls Reconnective Healing.

00:01:00.928 --> 00:01:02.329 align:middle line:84%
Eric is here to
share this with us.

00:01:02.329 --> 00:01:04.298 align:middle line:84%
Thank you so much
for joining me.

00:01:04.298 --> 00:01:05.933 align:middle line:84%
Thank you for having
me on the show.

00:01:05.933 --> 00:01:08.869 align:middle line:84%
You have contributed so
much to people's healing.

00:01:08.869 --> 00:01:13.440 align:middle line:84%
It's a pleasure to have you here
to learn about your life story.

00:01:13.440 --> 00:01:16.777 align:middle line:84%
What was life like
as a young child?

00:01:16.777 --> 00:01:18.111 align:middle line:84%
Did you know that
you had healing

00:01:18.111 --> 00:01:19.279 align:middle line:90%
abilities when you were young?

00:01:19.279 --> 00:01:22.316 align:middle line:84%
I don't think I
noticed anything

00:01:22.316 --> 00:01:24.885 align:middle line:84%
particularly different,
particularly distinct.

00:01:28.055 --> 00:01:30.357 align:middle line:84%
I will tell you, I was born
through a strange process.

00:01:30.357 --> 00:01:32.326 align:middle line:10%
My mother died
giving birth to me

00:01:32.326 --> 00:01:35.795 align:middle line:10%
and came back to life at a
time where that type of thing

00:01:35.795 --> 00:01:39.232 align:middle line:10%
was not discussed, the life
after death experience.

00:01:39.232 --> 00:01:42.402 align:middle line:10%
We didn't have Elisabeth
Kubler-Ross or Raymond Moody

00:01:42.402 --> 00:01:45.372 align:middle line:10%
or Dannion Brinkley or
any of the other people

00:01:45.372 --> 00:01:46.372 align:middle line:10%
who speak about it.

00:01:46.372 --> 00:01:50.676 align:middle line:84%
And I believe when I was around
six, give or take a year,

00:01:50.676 --> 00:01:54.581 align:middle line:84%
she shared her experience with
me and all of the insights

00:01:54.581 --> 00:01:56.483 align:middle line:84%
that she learned
in that process.

00:01:56.483 --> 00:01:58.551 align:middle line:90%
You remember that at six.

00:01:58.551 --> 00:02:00.654 align:middle line:84%
It was really
quite interesting.

00:02:00.654 --> 00:02:03.323 align:middle line:84%
You see, she was--
I'll do this briefly,

00:02:03.323 --> 00:02:06.526 align:middle line:84%
but she was on the
delivery table.

00:02:06.526 --> 00:02:10.663 align:middle line:84%
And she felt and heard the sound
of motors starting at her feet,

00:02:10.663 --> 00:02:12.399 align:middle line:84%
moving up to her
ankles and her knees.

00:02:12.399 --> 00:02:14.668 align:middle line:84%
And she couldn't understand
why no one else in the room

00:02:14.668 --> 00:02:16.436 align:middle line:90%
seemed to be responding to it.

00:02:16.436 --> 00:02:18.704 align:middle line:84%
And it kept climbing
up in her body.

00:02:18.704 --> 00:02:21.074 align:middle line:84%
And she knew that if
it got to her heart

00:02:21.074 --> 00:02:22.109 align:middle line:90%
that it would be the end.

00:02:22.109 --> 00:02:25.012 align:middle line:84%
And she just couldn't get
anyone's attention to stop it.

00:02:25.012 --> 00:02:27.714 align:middle line:84%
And the next thing she
knows, it was at her heart

00:02:27.714 --> 00:02:29.449 align:middle line:90%
and she had left her body.

00:02:29.449 --> 00:02:32.119 align:middle line:84%
And she started
passing through levels

00:02:32.119 --> 00:02:34.654 align:middle line:90%
of spirit or being or souls.

00:02:34.654 --> 00:02:38.191 align:middle line:84%
The first layer were
people who hadn't realized

00:02:38.191 --> 00:02:39.359 align:middle line:90%
that their life was quite over.

00:02:39.359 --> 00:02:42.662 align:middle line:84%
They felt incomplete, that they
still more things to do here.

00:02:42.662 --> 00:02:45.365 align:middle line:84%
The second layer or level of
people she doesn't recall.

00:02:45.365 --> 00:02:47.701 align:middle line:84%
The third one was the only
one that was uncomfortable.

00:02:47.701 --> 00:02:50.871 align:middle line:84%
It was uncomfortable to pass
through and uncomfortable

00:02:50.871 --> 00:02:52.672 align:middle line:90%
for the people on that level.

00:02:52.672 --> 00:02:55.409 align:middle line:84%
And those were the people who
did the only one thing that we

00:02:55.409 --> 00:02:59.312 align:middle line:84%
can do to temporarily
interrupt, shall we say,

00:02:59.312 --> 00:03:02.215 align:middle line:84%
God's plan, which was they
had taken their own life.

00:03:02.215 --> 00:03:04.751 align:middle line:84%
And she did get a
sense that eventually

00:03:04.751 --> 00:03:08.088 align:middle line:84%
they would step back into the
system and continue moving.

00:03:08.088 --> 00:03:10.724 align:middle line:84%
She eventually found
herself up at a light,

00:03:10.724 --> 00:03:14.795 align:middle line:84%
at a level where she
was being drawn down

00:03:14.795 --> 00:03:17.831 align:middle line:84%
a lane towards a bright
light, which is what she feels

00:03:17.831 --> 00:03:19.766 align:middle line:84%
most people speak
about as a feeling

00:03:19.766 --> 00:03:22.035 align:middle line:90%
of moving through a tunnel.

00:03:22.035 --> 00:03:23.904 align:middle line:84%
Her feet weren't
moving, but she was

00:03:23.904 --> 00:03:25.739 align:middle line:90%
gliding down towards that lane.

00:03:25.739 --> 00:03:30.544 align:middle line:84%
She was passing and seeing
colors-- flowers of colors

00:03:30.544 --> 00:03:33.814 align:middle line:84%
she had never before
seen, seeing people

00:03:33.814 --> 00:03:36.316 align:middle line:84%
from her current
lifetime and recognizing

00:03:36.316 --> 00:03:38.585 align:middle line:84%
the roles that we all play
in one another's lifetime.

00:03:38.585 --> 00:03:40.153 align:middle line:84%
This is all while
giving birth to you?

00:03:40.153 --> 00:03:40.853 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:03:40.853 --> 00:03:43.256 align:middle line:84%
They were sort of
guiding the way,

00:03:43.256 --> 00:03:45.392 align:middle line:84%
intimating the way to
move towards the light.

00:03:45.392 --> 00:03:47.561 align:middle line:84%
She didn't want to look at the
light because it was so bright.

00:03:47.561 --> 00:03:49.596 align:middle line:84%
She was afraid that it
would hurt her eyes.

00:03:49.596 --> 00:03:50.964 align:middle line:90%
But she felt compelled to look.

00:03:50.964 --> 00:03:53.834 align:middle line:84%
And when she did look, she
found that it didn't her eyes

00:03:53.834 --> 00:03:56.303 align:middle line:84%
and that there was nothing
physical to hold onto.

00:03:56.303 --> 00:03:58.405 align:middle line:84%
And suddenly she was
imbued with insights,

00:03:58.405 --> 00:04:01.608 align:middle line:84%
how ridiculous it is for us to
judge others in the way that

00:04:01.608 --> 00:04:06.680 align:middle line:84%
they look physically,
why the world is round,

00:04:06.680 --> 00:04:08.715 align:middle line:84%
why grass is green,
why the sky is blue,

00:04:08.715 --> 00:04:14.788 align:middle line:84%
how we cannot judge even God
for things that are seemingly

00:04:14.788 --> 00:04:17.089 align:middle line:84%
unexplainable, such
as drive-by shootings,

00:04:17.089 --> 00:04:20.994 align:middle line:84%
how utterly absurd it is for
young men and women to go out

00:04:20.994 --> 00:04:23.897 align:middle line:84%
losing their lives fighting
battles for older men

00:04:23.897 --> 00:04:25.532 align:middle line:84%
and women and
governments, that war is

00:04:25.532 --> 00:04:27.334 align:middle line:90%
a temporary state of barbarism.

00:04:27.334 --> 00:04:28.902 align:middle line:84%
You're recounting
this like it was you.

00:04:32.739 --> 00:04:36.676 align:middle line:84%
The second chapter of "The
Reconnection," my book,

00:04:36.676 --> 00:04:38.612 align:middle line:90%
is a retelling of this story.

00:04:38.612 --> 00:04:41.748 align:middle line:84%
And it was the most
difficult chapter to write,

00:04:41.748 --> 00:04:43.750 align:middle line:84%
because I had to go
back and forth a lot,

00:04:43.750 --> 00:04:45.552 align:middle line:84%
spend a lot of time with my
mother on the phone trying

00:04:45.552 --> 00:04:48.355 align:middle line:84%
to find words for things
that she said we don't

00:04:48.355 --> 00:04:52.526 align:middle line:90%
really have the words here for.

00:04:52.526 --> 00:04:55.762 align:middle line:84%
She understood how
there was a reason

00:04:55.762 --> 00:04:57.898 align:middle line:84%
for everything and everything
makes perfect sense when

00:04:57.898 --> 00:04:59.599 align:middle line:90%
you're there.

00:04:59.599 --> 00:05:01.801 align:middle line:84%
But you're not supposed to
know it when you're here.

00:05:01.801 --> 00:05:03.570 align:middle line:84%
Her life was laid
out before her.

00:05:03.570 --> 00:05:04.638 align:middle line:90%
She knew it was a good life.

00:05:04.638 --> 00:05:08.175 align:middle line:84%
Yet there was no judgment--
a seemingly contradictory

00:05:08.175 --> 00:05:09.809 align:middle line:84%
concept, but that's
because we view

00:05:09.809 --> 00:05:13.880 align:middle line:84%
everything here linearly in
our four-dimensional existence.

00:05:13.880 --> 00:05:16.149 align:middle line:84%
And that's a more
multi-dimensional existence.

00:05:16.149 --> 00:05:20.720 align:middle line:84%
And then, the funny thing was,
for such a beautiful place--

00:05:20.720 --> 00:05:23.723 align:middle line:84%
and she did say there was one
regret and only one regret

00:05:23.723 --> 00:05:26.026 align:middle line:84%
that people who
leave the body have,

00:05:26.026 --> 00:05:31.097 align:middle line:84%
that those who are left behind
mourn them because they don't

00:05:31.097 --> 00:05:33.166 align:middle line:84%
realize what a
beautiful place it is,

00:05:33.166 --> 00:05:34.634 align:middle line:84%
how really it's
all home, and how

00:05:34.634 --> 00:05:38.071 align:middle line:84%
really almost instantaneously
we're there together.

00:05:38.071 --> 00:05:41.942 align:middle line:84%
And then, suddenly, she felt
herself being sent back.

00:05:41.942 --> 00:05:44.311 align:middle line:84%
And for all the struggling
she did not to die, not

00:05:44.311 --> 00:05:47.581 align:middle line:84%
to leave in the first place, now
she didn't want to leave there.

00:05:47.581 --> 00:05:49.582 align:middle line:84%
But she felt herself
being sent back.

00:05:49.582 --> 00:05:51.718 align:middle line:84%
She was told she had
to raise her son.

00:05:51.718 --> 00:05:53.687 align:middle line:84%
And she felt all
of the insights she

00:05:53.687 --> 00:05:57.490 align:middle line:84%
was given being deprogrammed
from her, shall we say.

00:05:57.490 --> 00:05:58.558 align:middle line:90%
They were programmed to leave.

00:05:58.558 --> 00:06:01.461 align:middle line:84%
We're not supposed to have
those insights when we're here.

00:06:01.461 --> 00:06:03.597 align:middle line:84%
And she struggled hard
to hold onto these,

00:06:03.597 --> 00:06:05.832 align:middle line:84%
and some of the ones
she came back with.

00:06:05.832 --> 00:06:10.570 align:middle line:84%
And what was interesting-- what
was interesting about this is--

00:06:10.570 --> 00:06:11.805 align:middle line:84%
Go ahead.
Have some water.

00:06:11.805 --> 00:06:17.244 align:middle line:84%
What was interesting about this
is, when she came out of this,

00:06:17.244 --> 00:06:21.314 align:middle line:84%
she no longer had a fear of
death that she had always had.

00:06:21.314 --> 00:06:23.383 align:middle line:90%
She no longer had it.

00:06:23.383 --> 00:06:27.988 align:middle line:84%
And once she explained it to
me, I no longer had it either.

00:06:27.988 --> 00:06:30.156 align:middle line:90%
I look forward to being there.

00:06:30.156 --> 00:06:32.659 align:middle line:84%
Now, don't confuse
that with-- I don't

00:06:32.659 --> 00:06:34.159 align:middle line:90%
plan to hurry up my life here.

00:06:34.159 --> 00:06:35.996 align:middle line:90%
I'm not ready to leave.

00:06:35.996 --> 00:06:37.197 align:middle line:90%
I have more things to do.

00:06:37.197 --> 00:06:40.400 align:middle line:84%
I'm sticking around for a while,
much to some people's dismay

00:06:40.400 --> 00:06:42.302 align:middle line:90%
possibly.

00:06:42.302 --> 00:06:45.705 align:middle line:84%
But I look very much forward
to that experience as well.

00:06:45.705 --> 00:06:49.376 align:middle line:84%
So, you were raised by a
mother who had insights that

00:06:49.376 --> 00:06:51.945 align:middle line:90%
were beyond normal insights.

00:06:51.945 --> 00:06:55.215 align:middle line:84%
You were raised by someone who
introduced you to the world

00:06:55.215 --> 00:06:57.250 align:middle line:90%
of healing very early on.

00:06:57.250 --> 00:07:03.056 align:middle line:84%
She had a larger
spiritual awareness.

00:07:03.056 --> 00:07:06.593 align:middle line:84%
Now, remember, the
things that we know,

00:07:06.593 --> 00:07:12.799 align:middle line:84%
we don't always get
to be the message.

00:07:12.799 --> 00:07:15.335 align:middle line:84%
We can be the messenger
and not always the message.

00:07:15.335 --> 00:07:18.104 align:middle line:84%
For example, she learned how
ridiculous it was to judge

00:07:18.104 --> 00:07:19.239 align:middle line:90%
people on their appearance.

00:07:19.239 --> 00:07:23.109 align:middle line:84%
And she remembers waking
up in the hospital bed,

00:07:23.109 --> 00:07:25.545 align:middle line:84%
after giving delivery
to me, looking over

00:07:25.545 --> 00:07:29.549 align:middle line:84%
at the next bed and the woman in
it and going, boy, is she ugly.

00:07:29.549 --> 00:07:31.484 align:middle line:84%
And then she laughed to
herself, she said, now,

00:07:31.484 --> 00:07:33.520 align:middle line:84%
didn't I just learn
not to do that?

00:07:33.520 --> 00:07:36.623 align:middle line:84%
Or not to be afraid of
little things such as germs.

00:07:36.623 --> 00:07:39.058 align:middle line:84%
And yet at the same
time, she was always

00:07:39.058 --> 00:07:42.829 align:middle line:84%
disinfecting and keeping my
milk bottle clear and aware

00:07:42.829 --> 00:07:45.365 align:middle line:90%
of the contradictions in it.

00:07:45.365 --> 00:07:54.140 align:middle line:84%
I have a message in the
teachings of this healing work.

00:07:54.140 --> 00:07:56.876 align:middle line:90%
And I wish I were the message.

00:07:56.876 --> 00:08:02.215 align:middle line:84%
I know most people out there
in this and related fields,

00:08:02.215 --> 00:08:04.384 align:middle line:84%
many of them live
closer to their message.

00:08:04.384 --> 00:08:06.920 align:middle line:84%
Many of them live further
from their message.

00:08:06.920 --> 00:08:11.925 align:middle line:84%
No one seems to fully be the
message, and I'm not either.

00:08:11.925 --> 00:08:13.860 align:middle line:90%
I disappoint myself from it.

00:08:13.860 --> 00:08:16.696 align:middle line:84%
I sometimes berate
myself about it.

00:08:16.696 --> 00:08:19.399 align:middle line:84%
I tell myself I won't make
the same mistakes again.

00:08:19.399 --> 00:08:22.268 align:middle line:84%
I tell myself I won't be
so hard on myself again.

00:08:22.268 --> 00:08:25.972 align:middle line:84%
And yet then I do
the very same things.

00:08:25.972 --> 00:08:28.775 align:middle line:84%
A lot of people
say to me, why do

00:08:28.775 --> 00:08:29.976 align:middle line:84%
you think you were
chosen to bring

00:08:29.976 --> 00:08:31.111 align:middle line:90%
through this level of healing?

00:08:31.111 --> 00:08:34.748 align:middle line:84%
And I say, well, I certainly
wouldn't have picked me.

00:08:34.748 --> 00:08:36.216 align:middle line:90%
I know my past life.

00:08:36.216 --> 00:08:37.984 align:middle line:90%
I know my present life.

00:08:37.984 --> 00:08:42.688 align:middle line:84%
I don't have the patience
that healers should have.

00:08:42.688 --> 00:08:45.191 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes in the seminars when
someone asks a question I've

00:08:45.191 --> 00:08:48.395 align:middle line:84%
answered three or four times,
I'll turn around and I say,

00:08:48.395 --> 00:08:51.264 align:middle line:84%
I'll answer this again, but
really, weren't you listening?

00:08:51.264 --> 00:08:53.900 align:middle line:84%
And I'll say to myself, I'm
not going to say that again.

00:08:53.900 --> 00:08:55.869 align:middle line:90%
And yet I do say it again.

00:08:55.869 --> 00:08:59.906 align:middle line:84%
So you're human and
proclaiming to be enlightened.

00:08:59.906 --> 00:09:02.876 align:middle line:84%
But you have a-- did
you have any experiences

00:09:02.876 --> 00:09:05.478 align:middle line:84%
when you were a
child that you felt

00:09:05.478 --> 00:09:07.247 align:middle line:84%
that you were a chosen one?
-No.

00:09:07.247 --> 00:09:09.215 align:middle line:84%
I don't gather
that you did, yes.

00:09:09.215 --> 00:09:09.916 align:middle line:90%
I didn't.

00:09:09.916 --> 00:09:12.786 align:middle line:84%
I had some fun experiences
that in looking back at

00:09:12.786 --> 00:09:14.988 align:middle line:90%
them seem a little bit odd.

00:09:14.988 --> 00:09:17.123 align:middle line:84%
They didn't seem strong
enough at the time

00:09:17.123 --> 00:09:18.858 align:middle line:90%
to signal anything to me.

00:09:18.858 --> 00:09:26.332 align:middle line:84%
But for example, my grandfather
just held onto his watches

00:09:26.332 --> 00:09:27.033 align:middle line:90%
for some reason.

00:09:27.033 --> 00:09:28.968 align:middle line:84%
The watch would break, he'd
take it to the watchmaker.

00:09:28.968 --> 00:09:31.004 align:middle line:84%
It would break again,
take it to the watchmaker.

00:09:31.004 --> 00:09:32.906 align:middle line:84%
When the watchmaker
couldn't fix it again,

00:09:32.906 --> 00:09:35.375 align:middle line:84%
he just for some reason
couldn't throw it away.

00:09:35.375 --> 00:09:38.678 align:middle line:84%
So he had this box of old
watches that were broken.

00:09:38.678 --> 00:09:40.613 align:middle line:90%
One day he gave me the watches.

00:09:40.613 --> 00:09:43.249 align:middle line:84%
I found that I could
hold the watches,

00:09:43.249 --> 00:09:45.051 align:middle line:90%
and they would restart.

00:09:45.051 --> 00:09:48.021 align:middle line:84%
Now, this is just the
opposite of most people

00:09:48.021 --> 00:09:51.357 align:middle line:84%
who are in a strange
biochemical balance.

00:09:51.357 --> 00:09:53.893 align:middle line:84%
Most people either
wear watches fine

00:09:53.893 --> 00:09:56.095 align:middle line:84%
or they break watches
by wearing them.

00:09:56.095 --> 00:09:57.163 align:middle line:90%
I could restart them.

00:09:57.163 --> 00:09:59.432 align:middle line:84%
Would I say that that makes
me some special being?

00:09:59.432 --> 00:10:04.270 align:middle line:84%
No, it just happened to be
some freak little event.

00:10:04.270 --> 00:10:07.941 align:middle line:84%
I had an interesting situation
happen when I was putting

00:10:07.941 --> 00:10:09.375 align:middle line:84%
myself through
chiropractic school--

00:10:09.375 --> 00:10:12.045 align:middle line:84%
or when my family was putting
me through chiropractor school

00:10:12.045 --> 00:10:17.016 align:middle line:84%
and I was working on the
side as a shoe salesman.

00:10:17.016 --> 00:10:20.954 align:middle line:84%
And someone came in
and was buying shoes,

00:10:20.954 --> 00:10:25.024 align:middle line:84%
and they happened to work
at the place in Los Angeles

00:10:25.024 --> 00:10:26.793 align:middle line:84%
seismology lab,
where they measure

00:10:26.793 --> 00:10:29.295 align:middle line:90%
and anticipate for earthquakes.

00:10:29.295 --> 00:10:30.530 align:middle line:84%
And one of them said
to me, you know,

00:10:30.530 --> 00:10:33.500 align:middle line:84%
we're actually expecting a very
large earthquake on Wednesday.

00:10:33.500 --> 00:10:35.602 align:middle line:84%
I said, did you say anything to
anyone else here at the store?

00:10:35.602 --> 00:10:37.270 align:middle line:84%
They said, no.
I said, well, do me a favor.

00:10:37.270 --> 00:10:37.971 align:middle line:90%
Don't.

00:10:37.971 --> 00:10:40.607 align:middle line:84%
And when they left, I said to
a couple of people, you know,

00:10:40.607 --> 00:10:43.710 align:middle line:84%
I really think there's going to
be an earthquake-- to be funny.

00:10:43.710 --> 00:10:46.045 align:middle line:84%
And there was an earthquake that
came on Wednesday, so everyone

00:10:46.045 --> 00:10:47.814 align:middle line:90%
was very excited about it.

00:10:47.814 --> 00:10:49.215 align:middle line:90%
And people would ask me again.

00:10:49.215 --> 00:10:51.684 align:middle line:84%
And I found that there
were certain things that

00:10:51.684 --> 00:10:53.786 align:middle line:84%
would trigger in
my awareness that I

00:10:53.786 --> 00:10:55.154 align:middle line:84%
could say I believe
that there'll

00:10:55.154 --> 00:10:57.724 align:middle line:90%
be an earthquake on this day.

00:10:57.724 --> 00:10:58.691 align:middle line:90%
And it came about.

00:10:58.691 --> 00:11:01.628 align:middle line:84%
And it worked really well
for a couple of years,

00:11:01.628 --> 00:11:03.396 align:middle line:84%
until someone got
angry at me and said,

00:11:03.396 --> 00:11:04.664 align:middle line:90%
stop predicting gloom.

00:11:04.664 --> 00:11:06.999 align:middle line:84%
And all of a sudden, I
felt nervous about it,

00:11:06.999 --> 00:11:08.301 align:middle line:90%
and I stopped.

00:11:08.301 --> 00:11:11.271 align:middle line:84%
I don't think that this
is anyone's special gift.

00:11:11.271 --> 00:11:15.575 align:middle line:84%
I think that what happens is we
really tune in to what science

00:11:15.575 --> 00:11:17.744 align:middle line:90%
today calls zero point field.

00:11:17.744 --> 00:11:19.746 align:middle line:84%
We tune into this
field of awareness.

00:11:19.746 --> 00:11:21.548 align:middle line:90%
We're aware of it as kids.

00:11:21.548 --> 00:11:23.783 align:middle line:84%
School kids on a bus,
one child falls asleep,

00:11:23.783 --> 00:11:25.752 align:middle line:84%
another child stares at
them until they wake up.

00:11:25.752 --> 00:11:26.786 align:middle line:90%
We're in the field.

00:11:26.786 --> 00:11:28.054 align:middle line:84%
You think about a
friend you haven't

00:11:28.054 --> 00:11:29.289 align:middle line:90%
thought about for 15 years.

00:11:29.289 --> 00:11:31.958 align:middle line:84%
15 minutes later, the phone
rings, you're in the field.

00:11:31.958 --> 00:11:33.593 align:middle line:84%
People who are
psychics, people who

00:11:33.593 --> 00:11:35.862 align:middle line:84%
are geniuses, people
who are healers--

00:11:35.862 --> 00:11:37.263 align:middle line:90%
it's no special secret.

00:11:37.263 --> 00:11:39.766 align:middle line:84%
They're just listening a
little more here, a little more

00:11:39.766 --> 00:11:43.870 align:middle line:84%
here, and not second guessing
the information that comes in.

00:11:43.870 --> 00:11:46.306 align:middle line:84%
When we judge ourselves,
we second guess.

00:11:46.306 --> 00:11:51.477 align:middle line:84%
When we learn to observe without
judgment, we receive more.

00:11:51.477 --> 00:11:53.146 align:middle line:90%
We participate more.

00:11:53.146 --> 00:11:56.415 align:middle line:84%
We become more at one
with the universe.

00:11:56.415 --> 00:11:58.985 align:middle line:84%
And the practice also
helps the more you do that,

00:11:58.985 --> 00:12:03.957 align:middle line:84%
the more you become trusting
of the veil being thinner.

00:12:03.957 --> 00:12:05.825 align:middle line:90%
So what happened, though?

00:12:05.825 --> 00:12:08.394 align:middle line:84%
You had a pinnacle events
that came into your life

00:12:08.394 --> 00:12:11.397 align:middle line:84%
as you were in practice
now, as a chiropractor.

00:12:11.397 --> 00:12:13.666 align:middle line:84%
You had a full,
thriving practice.

00:12:13.666 --> 00:12:16.369 align:middle line:84%
And what happened one day
when a friend of yours

00:12:16.369 --> 00:12:20.740 align:middle line:90%
took you to a psychic?

00:12:20.740 --> 00:12:24.377 align:middle line:84%
I was introduced to this woman
on the beach reading cards.

00:12:24.377 --> 00:12:26.512 align:middle line:84%
She gave me a card reading,
nothing that stood out

00:12:26.512 --> 00:12:28.147 align:middle line:84%
in my head as particularly--
-Just a random event.

00:12:28.147 --> 00:12:29.782 align:middle line:90%
You just went with a friend.

00:12:29.782 --> 00:12:31.651 align:middle line:90%
Uh-huh.

00:12:31.651 --> 00:12:34.821 align:middle line:84%
And the woman said
to me, you know,

00:12:34.821 --> 00:12:37.323 align:middle line:84%
there's this work that I do,
and you need to have it done.

00:12:37.323 --> 00:12:39.292 align:middle line:90%
So I asked her to explain it.

00:12:39.292 --> 00:12:41.160 align:middle line:84%
And she said, well, you
see the meridian lines that

00:12:41.160 --> 00:12:43.663 align:middle line:84%
are on our bodies used to be
part of a much more powerful

00:12:43.663 --> 00:12:45.264 align:middle line:90%
system than they are today.

00:12:45.264 --> 00:12:46.933 align:middle line:84%
They would extend
off of our bodies,

00:12:46.933 --> 00:12:49.202 align:middle line:84%
tie into the grid lines
that encircle the planet,

00:12:49.202 --> 00:12:51.671 align:middle line:84%
encircle the globe,
and then continue out,

00:12:51.671 --> 00:12:54.173 align:middle line:84%
tying us into the rest of
the stars and the planets

00:12:54.173 --> 00:12:57.644 align:middle line:84%
and the dimensions in between--
and that at a certain point

00:12:57.644 --> 00:13:01.681 align:middle line:84%
in time, we, meaning
humanity, had

00:13:01.681 --> 00:13:04.083 align:middle line:90%
become disconnected from this.

00:13:04.083 --> 00:13:06.753 align:middle line:84%
Some people would attribute
that time to the Garden of Eden.

00:13:06.753 --> 00:13:10.289 align:middle line:84%
Different people, different
cultures have different time

00:13:10.289 --> 00:13:12.358 align:middle line:84%
frames where they
recognize or feel

00:13:12.358 --> 00:13:14.060 align:middle line:84%
that we were all one
with the universe,

00:13:14.060 --> 00:13:17.163 align:middle line:84%
and then there became
a human separation.

00:13:17.163 --> 00:13:20.033 align:middle line:84%
And as the universe
continues to evolve

00:13:20.033 --> 00:13:23.670 align:middle line:84%
at its grand and wondrous
rate, we've been evolving.

00:13:23.670 --> 00:13:25.838 align:middle line:84%
And eventually, over
generations, we'll

00:13:25.838 --> 00:13:29.075 align:middle line:84%
evolve to a point where we can
rejoin back into that system,

00:13:29.075 --> 00:13:32.478 align:middle line:84%
but that she could do work
that would tie us back

00:13:32.478 --> 00:13:34.747 align:middle line:84%
into it, sort of like
a giant, super-fast

00:13:34.747 --> 00:13:37.617 align:middle line:90%
DSL hook-up, or something.

00:13:37.617 --> 00:13:39.385 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, well,
this sounds intriguing.

00:13:39.385 --> 00:13:40.853 align:middle line:84%
How much money do you
want for the work.

00:13:40.853 --> 00:13:42.555 align:middle line:90%
And she said, $333.

00:13:42.555 --> 00:13:44.490 align:middle line:84%
And I said, no, thank you,
because I could think of lots

00:13:44.490 --> 00:13:47.226 align:middle line:84%
of things to do with
$333, and giving

00:13:47.226 --> 00:13:50.063 align:middle line:84%
them to a stranger on the beach
wasn't on the top of my list.

00:13:50.063 --> 00:13:51.330 align:middle line:84%
So I thanked her and
started to leave.

00:13:51.330 --> 00:13:54.333 align:middle line:84%
With the globe, with
the crystal ball.

00:13:54.333 --> 00:13:58.104 align:middle line:84%
So I thanked her very much
and I started to leave.

00:13:58.104 --> 00:14:00.406 align:middle line:84%
And she scribbled something down
on a piece of paper and said,

00:14:00.406 --> 00:14:02.141 align:middle line:84%
you can read about
it in a book called

00:14:02.141 --> 00:14:06.112 align:middle line:84%
"The Book of Knowledge, the
Keys of Enoch," chapter 317.

00:14:06.112 --> 00:14:08.448 align:middle line:90%
The author is Dr. JJ Hurtak.

00:14:08.448 --> 00:14:09.449 align:middle line:90%
So I thanked her.

00:14:09.449 --> 00:14:10.550 align:middle line:90%
I put the paper in my pocket.

00:14:10.550 --> 00:14:14.821 align:middle line:84%
I had no intention of paying
any attention to this again.

00:14:14.821 --> 00:14:16.989 align:middle line:84%
But I found I kept thinking
about it and thinking about it

00:14:16.989 --> 00:14:17.924 align:middle line:90%
and thinking about it.

00:14:17.924 --> 00:14:21.828 align:middle line:84%
So finally I walked into what
used to be called the Bodhi

00:14:21.828 --> 00:14:25.565 align:middle line:84%
Tree Bookstore in Los Angeles,
the big spiritual hub bookstore

00:14:25.565 --> 00:14:26.966 align:middle line:90%
there, at the time.

00:14:26.966 --> 00:14:30.236 align:middle line:84%
And I had an extra 10
minutes off from lunch.

00:14:30.236 --> 00:14:32.238 align:middle line:84%
So I took the book
down off the shelf.

00:14:32.238 --> 00:14:34.507 align:middle line:84%
They had it locked
away in glass and key.

00:14:34.507 --> 00:14:36.976 align:middle line:84%
And I figured I'll skim
through this chapter 317.

00:14:36.976 --> 00:14:38.511 align:middle line:90%
It's only eight little pages.

00:14:38.511 --> 00:14:39.612 align:middle line:90%
I'll quickly skim through it.

00:14:39.612 --> 00:14:40.880 align:middle line:90%
Have you ever seen that book?

00:14:40.880 --> 00:14:42.048 align:middle line:84%
-No, I have not.
-OK.

00:14:42.048 --> 00:14:43.616 align:middle line:84%
Well, let me tell you
that there are just three

00:14:43.616 --> 00:14:45.651 align:middle line:84%
things you cannot do with it.
-Skim?

00:14:45.651 --> 00:14:46.953 align:middle line:84%
You cannot quickly
skim through it.

00:14:46.953 --> 00:14:47.920 align:middle line:90%
You cannot read it.

00:14:47.920 --> 00:14:49.355 align:middle line:90%
And you cannot understand it.

00:14:49.355 --> 00:14:51.290 align:middle line:84%
And outside of that,
it's a great book.

00:14:51.290 --> 00:14:53.426 align:middle line:84%
The more I read, the
more confused I became.

00:14:53.426 --> 00:14:56.129 align:middle line:84%
The more confused,
the more intrigued.

00:14:56.129 --> 00:14:58.131 align:middle line:84%
I left the store,
I came back again.

00:14:58.131 --> 00:14:59.232 align:middle line:90%
I reread parts.

00:14:59.232 --> 00:15:00.767 align:middle line:84%
The parts I understood,
I didn't understand.

00:15:00.767 --> 00:15:02.068 align:middle line:84%
Well, you kept being
drawn back to it.

00:15:02.068 --> 00:15:04.504 align:middle line:84%
The parts I didn't
understand, I did understand.

00:15:04.504 --> 00:15:07.240 align:middle line:84%
Finally, after going back
and forth and back and forth,

00:15:07.240 --> 00:15:09.208 align:middle line:84%
I decided maybe it
would just be cheaper

00:15:09.208 --> 00:15:13.012 align:middle line:84%
if I paid the woman her $333
and let her do the work.

00:15:13.012 --> 00:15:14.113 align:middle line:90%
So I called her up.

00:15:14.113 --> 00:15:16.048 align:middle line:84%
She explained it was done
in two different days,

00:15:16.048 --> 00:15:17.383 align:middle line:90%
two different sessions.

00:15:17.383 --> 00:15:19.318 align:middle line:84%
I showed up on a
Thursday for part one.

00:15:19.318 --> 00:15:21.654 align:middle line:84%
She placed me on
a massage table,

00:15:21.654 --> 00:15:24.590 align:middle line:84%
dimmed the lights, put on the
new age tinkly music everyone's

00:15:24.590 --> 00:15:26.459 align:middle line:84%
grown to know and
love for some reason.

00:15:26.459 --> 00:15:28.494 align:middle line:84%
She started with
their fingertips

00:15:28.494 --> 00:15:31.097 align:middle line:84%
tracing little line patterns
on my face and my body.

00:15:31.097 --> 00:15:32.965 align:middle line:84%
All the while I'm
lying there thinking,

00:15:32.965 --> 00:15:36.235 align:middle line:84%
I cannot believe that this
woman is actually doing this

00:15:36.235 --> 00:15:39.005 align:middle line:90%
and I paid her money to do it.

00:15:39.005 --> 00:15:40.973 align:middle line:84%
So sitting there in
a state of disbelief.

00:15:40.973 --> 00:15:44.210 align:middle line:84%
And while lying there,
it suddenly dawned on me

00:15:44.210 --> 00:15:47.113 align:middle line:84%
that I'm not going to
gain anything out of going

00:15:47.113 --> 00:15:48.314 align:middle line:90%
on with my negative chatter.

00:15:48.314 --> 00:15:50.616 align:middle line:84%
So I might as well let
go and see what happens.

00:15:50.616 --> 00:15:52.285 align:middle line:84%
So with that, I let
myself drift off.

00:15:52.285 --> 00:15:55.288 align:middle line:84%
About another 45
minutes or so passes by.

00:15:55.288 --> 00:16:05.798 align:middle line:84%
She touches me gently, waking me
up with the grace and conscious

00:16:05.798 --> 00:16:08.401 align:middle line:84%
of someone who feels
that the Earth had moved,

00:16:08.401 --> 00:16:10.636 align:middle line:84%
except I seemed to be the
only one of the two of us

00:16:10.636 --> 00:16:11.871 align:middle line:90%
who didn't notice.

00:16:11.871 --> 00:16:13.239 align:middle line:90%
Get up slowly.

00:16:13.239 --> 00:16:14.707 align:middle line:90%
Stay in your body.

00:16:14.707 --> 00:16:15.708 align:middle line:90%
Keep your eyes closed.

00:16:15.708 --> 00:16:17.109 align:middle line:84%
Take your feet,
feel for the ground.

00:16:17.109 --> 00:16:19.579 align:middle line:84%
I'm thinking, isn't
it where I left it?

00:16:19.579 --> 00:16:21.147 align:middle line:84%
I don't know what
went on here, lady,

00:16:21.147 --> 00:16:23.382 align:middle line:90%
but I clearly missed this point.

00:16:23.382 --> 00:16:24.383 align:middle line:90%
I thanked her very much.

00:16:24.383 --> 00:16:27.486 align:middle line:84%
I went home thinking there was
nothing more ridiculous I could

00:16:27.486 --> 00:16:29.722 align:middle line:84%
possibly have done
except agreed to come

00:16:29.722 --> 00:16:32.124 align:middle line:90%
back for part two on Sunday.

00:16:32.124 --> 00:16:33.125 align:middle line:90%
I go home that night.

00:16:33.125 --> 00:16:34.160 align:middle line:90%
Everything seems normal.

00:16:34.160 --> 00:16:35.561 align:middle line:90%
I go to sleep.

00:16:35.561 --> 00:16:38.698 align:middle line:84%
About an hour
later, I'm awakened

00:16:38.698 --> 00:16:41.634 align:middle line:84%
in the middle of the night
by a very, very bright light.

00:16:41.634 --> 00:16:43.469 align:middle line:84%
I opened my eyes
to see what it was,

00:16:43.469 --> 00:16:47.707 align:middle line:84%
and it wasn't anything seemingly
attributable to something

00:16:47.707 --> 00:16:48.841 align:middle line:90%
spiritual or metaphysical.

00:16:48.841 --> 00:16:50.743 align:middle line:84%
It was just the
lamp next to my bed.

00:16:50.743 --> 00:16:52.245 align:middle line:90%
It had turned itself on.

00:16:52.245 --> 00:16:53.946 align:middle line:84%
Now, I had that
lamp for 10 years.

00:16:53.946 --> 00:16:55.848 align:middle line:84%
It hadn't selected
any other propitious

00:16:55.848 --> 00:16:57.083 align:middle line:90%
occasion to self-ignite.

00:16:57.083 --> 00:17:00.186 align:middle line:84%
But I figured, maybe it was an
electrical short, except shorts

00:17:00.186 --> 00:17:01.320 align:middle line:90%
usually turn things off.

00:17:01.320 --> 00:17:02.889 align:middle line:84%
And I don't think there's
an electrical long.

00:17:02.889 --> 00:17:07.526 align:middle line:84%
But I didn't think about it
that much, because what really

00:17:07.526 --> 00:17:12.665 align:middle line:84%
took over my
awareness quite eerily

00:17:12.665 --> 00:17:15.534 align:middle line:84%
was that it felt as if
somebody was in my house.

00:17:15.534 --> 00:17:19.839 align:middle line:84%
I can't tell you what an
uncomfortable feeling it

00:17:19.839 --> 00:17:21.173 align:middle line:84%
is to wake up and
feel that someone's

00:17:21.173 --> 00:17:23.175 align:middle line:84%
in your home, when no one
was there an hour or so ago

00:17:23.175 --> 00:17:23.943 align:middle line:90%
when you went to sleep.

00:17:23.943 --> 00:17:24.877 align:middle line:90%
Oh, yes, yes.

00:17:24.877 --> 00:17:25.711 align:middle line:90%
You just freeze.

00:17:25.711 --> 00:17:27.146 align:middle line:90%
You're just frozen.

00:17:27.146 --> 00:17:28.214 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:17:28.214 --> 00:17:30.149 align:middle line:84%
And then you realize
you're not going

00:17:30.149 --> 00:17:32.919 align:middle line:84%
to get anything out
of lying there frozen,

00:17:32.919 --> 00:17:34.153 align:middle line:84%
waiting to see
what might happen.

00:17:34.153 --> 00:17:34.854 align:middle line:90%
Not breathing.

00:17:34.854 --> 00:17:37.757 align:middle line:84%
So I got up very bravely
with, get this, a knife,

00:17:37.757 --> 00:17:39.959 align:middle line:84%
a can of pepper spray,
and my doberman pincher.

00:17:39.959 --> 00:17:41.227 align:middle line:84%
And I went marching
through the house?

00:17:41.227 --> 00:17:43.296 align:middle line:84%
You had all three of
those next to your bed?

00:17:43.296 --> 00:17:45.231 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:17:45.231 --> 00:17:47.466 align:middle line:84%
At that time, I had
a knife under my bed.

00:17:47.466 --> 00:17:49.769 align:middle line:84%
At that time, it
corresponded to when

00:17:49.769 --> 00:17:52.939 align:middle line:84%
I had taken a class a
while back, when pepper

00:17:52.939 --> 00:17:55.241 align:middle line:90%
spray classes were a big fad.

00:17:55.241 --> 00:17:57.443 align:middle line:84%
And yes, I had a
doberman pincher.

00:17:57.443 --> 00:17:59.578 align:middle line:84%
So I went hunting
through the house.

00:17:59.578 --> 00:18:00.579 align:middle line:90%
I couldn't find anyone.

00:18:00.579 --> 00:18:03.482 align:middle line:84%
And after about
20 minutes or so,

00:18:03.482 --> 00:18:07.119 align:middle line:84%
I realized that
it was most likely

00:18:07.119 --> 00:18:09.455 align:middle line:90%
my imagination, most likely.

00:18:09.455 --> 00:18:10.856 align:middle line:90%
I got back into bed.

00:18:10.856 --> 00:18:12.224 align:middle line:90%
I went to turn the lamp off.

00:18:12.224 --> 00:18:13.793 align:middle line:84%
And you know that little
round button we click

00:18:13.793 --> 00:18:15.494 align:middle line:90%
on and click off in lamps?

00:18:15.494 --> 00:18:17.630 align:middle line:84%
I'm a clicker, everything's
clicked into place.

00:18:17.630 --> 00:18:20.099 align:middle line:84%
Doors are shut,
toothpaste cap is on.

00:18:20.099 --> 00:18:21.701 align:middle line:90%
It wasn't clicked on.

00:18:21.701 --> 00:18:23.402 align:middle line:90%
It was just rotated halfway.

00:18:23.402 --> 00:18:25.871 align:middle line:84%
And I'm thinking, I
know that's not me.

00:18:25.871 --> 00:18:28.074 align:middle line:84%
But whatever it is, if they
let me wake up in the morning,

00:18:28.074 --> 00:18:28.841 align:middle line:90%
they let me wake up.

00:18:28.841 --> 00:18:31.010 align:middle line:84%
I might as well go to sleep or
I'll be a wreck for my patients

00:18:31.010 --> 00:18:31.711 align:middle line:90%
the next day.

00:18:31.711 --> 00:18:33.813 align:middle line:84%
The next day I go in to
work, it's a normal day.

00:18:33.813 --> 00:18:35.748 align:middle line:90%
Saturday's a normal Saturday.

00:18:35.748 --> 00:18:37.917 align:middle line:84%
Sunday I come back
in for part two.

00:18:37.917 --> 00:18:38.918 align:middle line:90%
Oh, you went back.

00:18:38.918 --> 00:18:39.785 align:middle line:90%
Ah.

00:18:39.785 --> 00:18:41.520 align:middle line:90%
I paid her $333.

00:18:41.520 --> 00:18:43.756 align:middle line:84%
You're getting
your money's worth.

00:18:43.756 --> 00:18:44.957 align:middle line:90%
Yes, I am.

00:18:44.957 --> 00:18:46.659 align:middle line:90%
So I go back for part two.

00:18:46.659 --> 00:18:50.129 align:middle line:84%
She lies me down on the table,
dims the lights, new age tinkly

00:18:50.129 --> 00:18:52.064 align:middle line:84%
music again, starts
with the fingers

00:18:52.064 --> 00:18:53.733 align:middle line:84%
and drawing the
lines on my body.

00:18:53.733 --> 00:18:55.234 align:middle line:90%
But this time it's different.

00:18:55.234 --> 00:18:56.736 align:middle line:90%
I can't seem to lie still.

00:18:56.736 --> 00:18:58.671 align:middle line:90%
My body is chilled.

00:18:58.671 --> 00:19:00.973 align:middle line:90%
It wants to move.

00:19:00.973 --> 00:19:02.875 align:middle line:84%
When she finished--
and mind you,

00:19:02.875 --> 00:19:05.511 align:middle line:84%
this was an oppressively
hot, hot, hot August

00:19:05.511 --> 00:19:07.947 align:middle line:84%
day in Southern California
in a non-air conditioned

00:19:07.947 --> 00:19:08.914 align:middle line:90%
one bedroom apartment.

00:19:08.914 --> 00:19:10.750 align:middle line:84%
When she finished,
I was so chilled

00:19:10.750 --> 00:19:14.286 align:middle line:84%
she had to wrap me in a blanket
for a good five minutes.

00:19:14.286 --> 00:19:16.689 align:middle line:84%
I remember leaving and
getting into my car,

00:19:16.689 --> 00:19:19.959 align:middle line:84%
I started the ignition,
began the drive.

00:19:19.959 --> 00:19:22.228 align:middle line:84%
I experienced a sense of
peace that on one hand

00:19:22.228 --> 00:19:24.563 align:middle line:84%
I had never known before,
and on the other hand,

00:19:24.563 --> 00:19:27.166 align:middle line:84%
it was more familiar than
anything I'd ever experienced.

00:19:27.166 --> 00:19:30.036 align:middle line:84%
I started the drive home, and
I don't remember another thing.

00:19:30.036 --> 00:19:31.904 align:middle line:90%
Don't recall a thing.

00:19:31.904 --> 00:19:34.306 align:middle line:90%
Don't recall arriving at home.

00:19:34.306 --> 00:19:35.975 align:middle line:84%
Don't recall going
to sleep that night.

00:19:35.975 --> 00:19:38.544 align:middle line:84%
Don't recall going in
to work the next day.

00:19:38.544 --> 00:19:42.982 align:middle line:84%
It was somewhere mid-morning,
my first recollection

00:19:42.982 --> 00:19:47.453 align:middle line:84%
is that I was standing in
a hallway in between some

00:19:47.453 --> 00:19:52.024 align:middle line:84%
of my chiropractic
adjustment rooms.

00:19:52.024 --> 00:19:54.427 align:middle line:84%
Two of my employees are
facing me, asking me

00:19:54.427 --> 00:19:57.797 align:middle line:84%
what happened over the weekend,
why I looked so different,

00:19:57.797 --> 00:19:59.465 align:middle line:90%
why I sounded so different.

00:19:59.465 --> 00:20:01.634 align:middle line:84%
And I didn't want to say,
well, I paid some very charming

00:20:01.634 --> 00:20:04.603 align:middle line:84%
Jewish gypsy who called me
bubellah $333 to draw lines

00:20:04.603 --> 00:20:05.638 align:middle line:90%
on my body with her fingertips.

00:20:05.638 --> 00:20:07.606 align:middle line:90%
Why do you ask?

00:20:07.606 --> 00:20:09.842 align:middle line:90%
So I gave a non-response.

00:20:09.842 --> 00:20:11.010 align:middle line:90%
I went into the next room.

00:20:11.010 --> 00:20:12.878 align:middle line:90%
I worked on the patient.

00:20:12.878 --> 00:20:15.581 align:middle line:84%
I told the patient, as always,
to just close their eyes,

00:20:15.581 --> 00:20:17.783 align:middle line:84%
relax for a minute or so
before they open their eyes

00:20:17.783 --> 00:20:18.951 align:middle line:90%
and got up.

00:20:18.951 --> 00:20:21.687 align:middle line:84%
When he opened his eyes, he said
to me, who walked into the room

00:20:21.687 --> 00:20:23.422 align:middle line:84%
while I was lying here?
I said, no one.

00:20:23.422 --> 00:20:24.323 align:middle line:90%
Why?

00:20:24.323 --> 00:20:25.891 align:middle line:84%
He said, no-- like
I didn't hear him.

00:20:25.891 --> 00:20:27.493 align:middle line:84%
Who walked into the room?
I said, no one.

00:20:27.493 --> 00:20:28.527 align:middle line:90%
He said, I heard them come in.

00:20:28.527 --> 00:20:29.328 align:middle line:90%
I said, no one came in.

00:20:29.328 --> 00:20:30.763 align:middle line:84%
He said, I heard them
standing at the door.

00:20:30.763 --> 00:20:31.530 align:middle line:90%
No one was at the door.

00:20:31.530 --> 00:20:33.466 align:middle line:84%
I went back and
forth, back and forth.

00:20:33.466 --> 00:20:34.633 align:middle line:90%
Finally, he said OK.

00:20:34.633 --> 00:20:37.403 align:middle line:84%
But I could tell he
didn't really believe me.

00:20:37.403 --> 00:20:39.305 align:middle line:90%
I didn't give it much thought.

00:20:39.305 --> 00:20:40.940 align:middle line:84%
I went in to see
my next patient.

00:20:40.940 --> 00:20:42.842 align:middle line:84%
When I finished with
her, she opened her eyes.

00:20:42.842 --> 00:20:45.244 align:middle line:84%
She said, who walked into the
room while I was lying there?

00:20:45.244 --> 00:20:46.378 align:middle line:90%
I said, no one, why?

00:20:46.378 --> 00:20:48.347 align:middle line:84%
She insisted the same story.
-Back and forth?

00:20:48.347 --> 00:20:52.318 align:middle line:84%
All in all, seven
patients in this one day

00:20:52.318 --> 00:20:54.854 align:middle line:84%
insisted that someone
came into the room,

00:20:54.854 --> 00:20:57.423 align:middle line:84%
stood there, walked around,
ran around, two of them

00:20:57.423 --> 00:20:59.458 align:middle line:84%
actually looked at me and
said it felt as if flying.

00:20:59.458 --> 00:21:01.160 align:middle line:84%
Someone was flying
around the ceiling.

00:21:01.160 --> 00:21:05.397 align:middle line:84%
Now, after 12 years in practice,
no one had ever said anything

00:21:05.397 --> 00:21:06.665 align:middle line:90%
to me like this before.

00:21:06.665 --> 00:21:08.701 align:middle line:84%
So seven people in one day,
you would think that this

00:21:08.701 --> 00:21:10.703 align:middle line:90%
would have gotten my attention.

00:21:10.703 --> 00:21:12.571 align:middle line:84%
But other patients
are saying, I can feel

00:21:12.571 --> 00:21:14.540 align:middle line:90%
your hands before you touch me.

00:21:14.540 --> 00:21:15.608 align:middle line:90%
Of course I didn't believe them.

00:21:15.608 --> 00:21:17.042 align:middle line:84%
I said, so lie down
and close your eyes.

00:21:17.042 --> 00:21:18.644 align:middle line:90%
They had their eyes closed.

00:21:18.644 --> 00:21:21.247 align:middle line:84%
I held my hands in different
directions, several feet

00:21:21.247 --> 00:21:23.449 align:middle line:90%
to several yards away from them.

00:21:23.449 --> 00:21:25.718 align:middle line:84%
They could tell me, it
was aimed toward the feet,

00:21:25.718 --> 00:21:26.952 align:middle line:84%
it was aimed towards
their shoulders.

00:21:26.952 --> 00:21:29.822 align:middle line:84%
I would see tiny little muscles
in their forehead or chin

00:21:29.822 --> 00:21:31.557 align:middle line:84%
ripple the way you drop
a pebble into water.

00:21:31.557 --> 00:21:33.225 align:middle line:90%
And it begins to ripple.

00:21:33.225 --> 00:21:36.795 align:middle line:84%
Involuntary muscles, muscles
we couldn't move by intention.

00:21:36.795 --> 00:21:39.031 align:middle line:84%
I would see their eyes
rapidly dart back and forth

00:21:39.031 --> 00:21:40.533 align:middle line:90%
when they'd open their eyes.

00:21:40.533 --> 00:21:42.001 align:middle line:84%
They would tell me
they were seeing colors

00:21:42.001 --> 00:21:44.003 align:middle line:84%
they had never before
seen, smelling flowers

00:21:44.003 --> 00:21:45.571 align:middle line:90%
they had never smelled before.

00:21:45.571 --> 00:21:47.540 align:middle line:84%
And they started
reporting healings.

00:21:47.540 --> 00:21:48.974 align:middle line:90%
Real healings.

00:21:48.974 --> 00:21:50.976 align:middle line:84%
They were getting up out
of wheelchairs, vision

00:21:50.976 --> 00:21:52.912 align:middle line:84%
and hearing returning,
children with cerebral palsy

00:21:52.912 --> 00:21:54.547 align:middle line:84%
and epilepsy--
-Oh, my goodness.

00:21:54.547 --> 00:21:57.383 align:middle line:84%
--were able to walk around
and play, not have seizures,

00:21:57.383 --> 00:21:59.485 align:middle line:84%
not need their medications,
their parents would call,

00:21:59.485 --> 00:22:00.352 align:middle line:90%
their doctors would call.

00:22:00.352 --> 00:22:01.687 align:middle line:90%
They'd say, what did you do?

00:22:01.687 --> 00:22:03.889 align:middle line:84%
I said, I didn't do anything,
and don't tell anyone.

00:22:03.889 --> 00:22:04.757 align:middle line:90%
Which went over about as--

00:22:04.757 --> 00:22:06.091 align:middle line:90%
Were you afraid of your gifts?

00:22:06.091 --> 00:22:07.159 align:middle line:90%
I mean, were you afraid of this?

00:22:07.159 --> 00:22:07.993 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:22:07.993 --> 00:22:08.694 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:22:12.498 --> 00:22:21.073 align:middle line:84%
I may have been-- I don't
know what the word is.

00:22:21.073 --> 00:22:25.544 align:middle line:84%
I was in awe of
something large, but I

00:22:25.544 --> 00:22:30.549 align:middle line:84%
don't know that I was
quite ready yet for people

00:22:30.549 --> 00:22:31.584 align:middle line:90%
to start talking about it.

00:22:31.584 --> 00:22:33.152 align:middle line:84%
To wrap your head around
it and to tell people

00:22:33.152 --> 00:22:33.852 align:middle line:90%
you were doing this.

00:22:33.852 --> 00:22:35.721 align:middle line:84%
I was just trying
to discover it.

00:22:35.721 --> 00:22:39.491 align:middle line:84%
I didn't want to lose
credibility with doctors

00:22:39.491 --> 00:22:40.993 align:middle line:90%
and other professionals.

00:22:40.993 --> 00:22:41.760 align:middle line:90%
A thriving practice.

00:22:41.760 --> 00:22:42.795 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:22:42.795 --> 00:22:46.198 align:middle line:84%
And soon people started
asking me to teach this.

00:22:46.198 --> 00:22:48.334 align:middle line:84%
And I said, teach it?
You've got to be nuts.

00:22:48.334 --> 00:22:49.868 align:middle line:84%
I'm standing there waving
my hands in the air,

00:22:49.868 --> 00:22:50.669 align:middle line:90%
looking like a fool.

00:22:50.669 --> 00:22:53.105 align:middle line:84%
So you go outside, wave
your hands in the air,

00:22:53.105 --> 00:22:54.940 align:middle line:84%
let me know what your
neighbors have to say about it.

00:22:54.940 --> 00:22:55.941 align:middle line:84%
See what they have to say.
Yes.

00:22:55.941 --> 00:22:57.743 align:middle line:84%
But more and more, my
patients would tell me,

00:22:57.743 --> 00:22:59.511 align:middle line:84%
I drove home after
my session with you.

00:22:59.511 --> 00:23:00.679 align:middle line:84%
I pulled up in
front of my house,

00:23:00.679 --> 00:23:03.148 align:middle line:84%
the automatic garage door
opened before I hit the button.

00:23:03.148 --> 00:23:06.085 align:middle line:84%
Or I walked inside, the lamp
or the TV turned off and on.

00:23:06.085 --> 00:23:07.086 align:middle line:90%
I felt sensations in my hands.

00:23:07.086 --> 00:23:09.588 align:middle line:84%
So the energy was
transferring to the patient

00:23:09.588 --> 00:23:11.523 align:middle line:84%
where they were
actually-- interesting.

00:23:11.523 --> 00:23:14.293 align:middle line:84%
Transmitting to them,
they held their hands

00:23:14.293 --> 00:23:15.361 align:middle line:90%
by someone in their family.

00:23:15.361 --> 00:23:16.862 align:middle line:84%
The father could walk
after the stroke.

00:23:16.862 --> 00:23:19.932 align:middle line:84%
Did you ever go back
and try to find the lady

00:23:19.932 --> 00:23:23.302 align:middle line:90%
that did the healing on you?

00:23:23.302 --> 00:23:26.372 align:middle line:84%
I was having
strange experiences.

00:23:26.372 --> 00:23:29.675 align:middle line:84%
The lamps were turning
on about twice a week.

00:23:29.675 --> 00:23:33.312 align:middle line:84%
There was a door open somewhere,
interior door of my home,

00:23:33.312 --> 00:23:34.713 align:middle line:90%
about twice a week.

00:23:34.713 --> 00:23:39.451 align:middle line:84%
If I slept at someone else's
home, it would happen there.

00:23:39.451 --> 00:23:42.121 align:middle line:84%
I would call her up and
say what was going on.

00:23:42.121 --> 00:23:43.856 align:middle line:84%
She'd give me new
age platitudes,

00:23:43.856 --> 00:23:45.524 align:middle line:84%
but she couldn't really
come up with answers.

00:23:45.524 --> 00:23:49.862 align:middle line:84%
But you see, the story
didn't yet become strange.

00:23:49.862 --> 00:23:52.631 align:middle line:84%
Did anything that she--
did she say that this was

00:23:52.631 --> 00:23:54.933 align:middle line:84%
an extraordinary
experience for her,

00:23:54.933 --> 00:23:58.003 align:middle line:84%
that this was unlike any
other healing she had done?

00:23:58.003 --> 00:23:58.804 align:middle line:90%
Not yet.

00:23:58.804 --> 00:24:04.576 align:middle line:84%
But then as I started to
work with the patients-- see,

00:24:04.576 --> 00:24:06.178 align:middle line:84%
I haven't told this
story for so long

00:24:06.178 --> 00:24:08.180 align:middle line:84%
that I'm trying to remember
it now so some of it

00:24:08.180 --> 00:24:08.947 align:middle line:90%
may be out of sequence.

00:24:08.947 --> 00:24:09.815 align:middle line:90%
You're doing a great job.

00:24:09.815 --> 00:24:10.816 align:middle line:90%
I'm involved.

00:24:10.816 --> 00:24:12.484 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:24:12.484 --> 00:24:16.288 align:middle line:84%
As I started doing the
healings with patients,

00:24:16.288 --> 00:24:19.224 align:middle line:84%
on more than one occasion,
my palm blistered.

00:24:19.224 --> 00:24:21.493 align:middle line:84%
Tiny little millimeter
sized blisters.

00:24:21.493 --> 00:24:23.996 align:middle line:84%
Not full sized ones,
millimeter sized blisters.

00:24:23.996 --> 00:24:27.032 align:middle line:84%
Instead of lasting--
what do blisters last,

00:24:27.032 --> 00:24:28.967 align:middle line:90%
a few days usually at least?

00:24:28.967 --> 00:24:31.537 align:middle line:84%
These were gone
inside a few hours.

00:24:31.537 --> 00:24:35.074 align:middle line:84%
On another occasion, my palm
bled, not like a stigmata

00:24:35.074 --> 00:24:35.808 align:middle line:90%
or anything like that.

00:24:35.808 --> 00:24:38.677 align:middle line:84%
This didn't scare you,
in any way frighten you,

00:24:38.677 --> 00:24:40.346 align:middle line:84%
make you think--
-No.

00:24:40.346 --> 00:24:41.714 align:middle line:84%
This was just a
little bit of blood,

00:24:41.714 --> 00:24:43.849 align:middle line:84%
like if you stick your
palm with a needle.

00:24:46.585 --> 00:24:48.687 align:middle line:90%
It excited me.

00:24:48.687 --> 00:24:52.057 align:middle line:84%
I knew I was standing in
the presence of something

00:24:52.057 --> 00:24:54.760 align:middle line:84%
so huge it couldn't
be interpreted.

00:24:54.760 --> 00:24:57.796 align:middle line:90%
I was more in a state of awe.

00:24:57.796 --> 00:24:59.331 align:middle line:84%
That's the closest
word I can tell you.

00:24:59.331 --> 00:25:02.134 align:middle line:84%
Now, awe can be
confused with fear.

00:25:02.134 --> 00:25:03.502 align:middle line:90%
But it was reverence.

00:25:03.502 --> 00:25:04.937 align:middle line:90%
But it was reverence.

00:25:04.937 --> 00:25:08.374 align:middle line:84%
It's sort of like, if you
listen to some interpretations

00:25:08.374 --> 00:25:11.009 align:middle line:84%
of the Bible, they talk
about being God fearing.

00:25:11.009 --> 00:25:12.945 align:middle line:84%
And that phrase never
made sense to me.

00:25:12.945 --> 00:25:16.515 align:middle line:84%
Why would a god want
us to be in fear?

00:25:16.515 --> 00:25:19.351 align:middle line:84%
And in looking back at
the original Hebrew,

00:25:19.351 --> 00:25:21.120 align:middle line:90%
it's a mistranslation.

00:25:21.120 --> 00:25:24.790 align:middle line:84%
The word that it was
taken from, [HEBREW],

00:25:24.790 --> 00:25:27.559 align:middle line:84%
on its most base
level could mean fear.

00:25:27.559 --> 00:25:30.696 align:middle line:84%
But on its highest level,
it means to be in awe.

00:25:30.696 --> 00:25:34.867 align:middle line:84%
It's someone who is in awe of
God, in awe of that presence.

00:25:34.867 --> 00:25:38.637 align:middle line:90%
And so then it got stranger.

00:25:38.637 --> 00:25:40.139 align:middle line:90%
Like this isn't strange enough.

00:25:40.139 --> 00:25:41.673 align:middle line:90%
No, no.

00:25:41.673 --> 00:25:44.777 align:middle line:84%
Because what happened was,
about four months into it,

00:25:44.777 --> 00:25:47.513 align:middle line:84%
I had a patient
come in to see me.

00:25:47.513 --> 00:25:50.082 align:middle line:84%
Now, this patient was a patient
of mine from a while back

00:25:50.082 --> 00:25:52.851 align:middle line:84%
but had been out of town
so wasn't coming in when

00:25:52.851 --> 00:25:54.119 align:middle line:90%
the healings were happening.

00:25:54.119 --> 00:25:56.288 align:middle line:84%
He showed up to
receive chiropractic.

00:25:56.288 --> 00:25:58.757 align:middle line:84%
I gave him his
chiropractic visits.

00:25:58.757 --> 00:26:01.193 align:middle line:84%
And then I told him, as I
always tell my patients,

00:26:01.193 --> 00:26:03.429 align:middle line:84%
just lie there with your
eyes closed for a moment.

00:26:03.429 --> 00:26:08.500 align:middle line:84%
But what I started doing was
sort of feeling the field,

00:26:08.500 --> 00:26:10.402 align:middle line:84%
shall we say, around them
while they were lying

00:26:10.402 --> 00:26:11.370 align:middle line:90%
there with their eyes closed.

00:26:11.370 --> 00:26:14.973 align:middle line:84%
And as I did that,
his head jerked back,

00:26:14.973 --> 00:26:16.542 align:middle line:84%
his eyes rolled to
the top of his head,

00:26:16.542 --> 00:26:18.677 align:middle line:84%
his mouth opened, his
tongue started to move,

00:26:18.677 --> 00:26:21.413 align:middle line:84%
his arms were sort
of gently swaying.

00:26:21.413 --> 00:26:25.284 align:middle line:84%
And air audibly
escaped his mouth.

00:26:25.284 --> 00:26:26.852 align:middle line:84%
You could see from
the way his tongue was

00:26:26.852 --> 00:26:29.121 align:middle line:84%
moving that he was speaking, but
you couldn't really hear words.

00:26:29.121 --> 00:26:32.324 align:middle line:84%
As a matter of fact, I brought
my ear close to listen.

00:26:32.324 --> 00:26:33.959 align:middle line:84%
And I did hear a
voice-- which I used

00:26:33.959 --> 00:26:36.462 align:middle line:84%
to say it's the voice of our
mothers we all carry with us.

00:26:36.462 --> 00:26:37.362 align:middle line:90%
I've changed my mind.

00:26:37.362 --> 00:26:40.499 align:middle line:84%
It's the voice of my mother
we all carry with us-- saying,

00:26:40.499 --> 00:26:41.233 align:middle line:90%
what are you doing?

00:26:41.233 --> 00:26:43.168 align:middle line:84%
Get your ear away from
that crazy person.

00:26:43.168 --> 00:26:44.736 align:middle line:90%
He might bite you.

00:26:44.736 --> 00:26:46.104 align:middle line:84%
So I can't explain
what it's like to be

00:26:46.104 --> 00:26:48.073 align:middle line:84%
struck funny and freaked
out at the same time.

00:26:48.073 --> 00:26:49.675 align:middle line:84%
But anyway, I realized
all the patients

00:26:49.675 --> 00:26:50.509 align:middle line:90%
were waiting to come in.

00:26:50.509 --> 00:26:51.643 align:middle line:90%
I had to stop.

00:26:51.643 --> 00:26:54.413 align:middle line:84%
So I sort of touched him
lightly and I let him stop.

00:26:54.413 --> 00:26:56.081 align:middle line:84%
And he didn't say
anything to me,

00:26:56.081 --> 00:26:57.349 align:middle line:90%
so I didn't say anything to him.

00:26:57.349 --> 00:26:58.383 align:middle line:90%
I mean, what am I going to say?

00:26:58.383 --> 00:26:59.318 align:middle line:90%
Hey, Fred, what's this?

00:26:59.318 --> 00:27:02.054 align:middle line:84%
You just start
speaking in tongue.

00:27:02.054 --> 00:27:03.956 align:middle line:90%
So he left.

00:27:03.956 --> 00:27:05.657 align:middle line:84%
But when he came back
on his next visit,

00:27:05.657 --> 00:27:06.825 align:middle line:90%
the same thing happened.

00:27:06.825 --> 00:27:08.694 align:middle line:84%
Now realize, he was a patient
of mine for a long time,

00:27:08.694 --> 00:27:10.162 align:middle line:90%
never did this before.

00:27:10.162 --> 00:27:11.497 align:middle line:84%
On his second visit,
the same thing

00:27:11.497 --> 00:27:15.033 align:middle line:84%
happened, but this time the air
condensed itself into a voice.

00:27:15.033 --> 00:27:18.003 align:middle line:84%
And the voice said, we are
here to tell you to continue

00:27:18.003 --> 00:27:19.671 align:middle line:90%
doing what you are doing.

00:27:19.671 --> 00:27:22.875 align:middle line:84%
What you are doing is
bringing light and information

00:27:22.875 --> 00:27:23.742 align:middle line:90%
onto the planet.

00:27:23.742 --> 00:27:28.580 align:middle line:84%
And if you heard this voice, you
knew to step back and listen.

00:27:28.580 --> 00:27:29.615 align:middle line:90%
What did you do?

00:27:29.615 --> 00:27:30.682 align:middle line:90%
What did you do?

00:27:30.682 --> 00:27:32.251 align:middle line:84%
Well, I was in
quite a bit of shock.

00:27:32.251 --> 00:27:35.387 align:middle line:84%
I finally-- my patients were
in my other rooms, again,

00:27:35.387 --> 00:27:37.789 align:middle line:84%
waiting for me.
So I touched him lightly.

00:27:37.789 --> 00:27:40.125 align:middle line:84%
And I said, Fred--
and this time,

00:27:40.125 --> 00:27:42.694 align:middle line:84%
he jumped up off of the table,
backed against the wall,

00:27:42.694 --> 00:27:46.798 align:middle line:84%
extended his arms out
blocking the wall phone,

00:27:46.798 --> 00:27:48.867 align:middle line:84%
because he was afraid I was
going to call a mental hospital

00:27:48.867 --> 00:27:50.235 align:middle line:90%
and have him taken away.

00:27:50.235 --> 00:27:52.004 align:middle line:84%
So he explained to
me that this voice

00:27:52.004 --> 00:27:54.940 align:middle line:84%
had come through him a few times
since he was a young child.

00:27:54.940 --> 00:27:56.675 align:middle line:84%
Only two people in his
life knew about it.

00:27:56.675 --> 00:27:57.976 align:middle line:90%
He didn't want anyone to know.

00:27:57.976 --> 00:27:59.344 align:middle line:84%
He felt it starting
on the last visit

00:27:59.344 --> 00:28:01.013 align:middle line:84%
but thought I didn't
notice anything.

00:28:01.013 --> 00:28:02.381 align:middle line:90%
And this time it got away.

00:28:02.381 --> 00:28:03.248 align:middle line:90%
And I thought, all right.

00:28:03.248 --> 00:28:05.484 align:middle line:90%
It's something unique to Fred.

00:28:05.484 --> 00:28:08.020 align:middle line:90%
That's all I attributed it to.

00:28:08.020 --> 00:28:10.656 align:middle line:84%
Two days later, three other
patients heads jerked,

00:28:10.656 --> 00:28:13.325 align:middle line:84%
eyes rolled, mouth open,
tongue moved, air came out.

00:28:13.325 --> 00:28:15.661 align:middle line:84%
I was not going to wait
for a double blind story

00:28:15.661 --> 00:28:18.463 align:middle line:84%
on their second--
and I know the show's

00:28:18.463 --> 00:28:20.799 align:middle line:84%
only so long, so I'm going to
skip the details around this.

00:28:20.799 --> 00:28:21.667 align:middle line:90%
It's a fascinating story.

00:28:21.667 --> 00:28:25.504 align:middle line:84%
Let's just say that
on their second visit,

00:28:25.504 --> 00:28:26.805 align:middle line:90%
they lost consciousness.

00:28:26.805 --> 00:28:29.274 align:middle line:84%
They spoke the same
two phrases Fred said.

00:28:29.274 --> 00:28:30.576 align:middle line:84%
We're here to tell
you to continue

00:28:30.576 --> 00:28:31.410 align:middle line:90%
doing what you're doing.

00:28:31.410 --> 00:28:33.779 align:middle line:84%
What you're doing is bringing
light and information

00:28:33.779 --> 00:28:34.479 align:middle line:90%
onto the planet.

00:28:34.479 --> 00:28:35.914 align:middle line:84%
Then two of them added
what you're doing

00:28:35.914 --> 00:28:37.349 align:middle line:90%
is reconnecting strands.

00:28:37.349 --> 00:28:40.185 align:middle line:84%
One of them said, what you're
doing is reconnecting strings.

00:28:40.185 --> 00:28:41.587 align:middle line:84%
Fred came back in
later that week

00:28:41.587 --> 00:28:45.891 align:middle line:84%
and said, what you're doing
is reconnecting strings.

00:28:45.891 --> 00:28:48.260 align:middle line:84%
A few days later, five
other patients, all in all,

00:28:48.260 --> 00:28:52.164 align:middle line:84%
there was a three-month period
of time where over 50, 5-0,

00:28:52.164 --> 00:28:54.433 align:middle line:84%
different patients
lost consciousness,

00:28:54.433 --> 00:29:00.305 align:middle line:84%
brought through six word
for word verbatim phrases.

00:29:00.305 --> 00:29:03.075 align:middle line:84%
And then it stopped
coming through everyone,

00:29:03.075 --> 00:29:06.044 align:middle line:84%
but it continued
coming through Fred.

00:29:06.044 --> 00:29:08.180 align:middle line:84%
Fred didn't like to talk
about this a whole lot,

00:29:08.180 --> 00:29:10.415 align:middle line:84%
but I could once in a
while coerce him to do it,

00:29:10.415 --> 00:29:12.150 align:middle line:90%
and I made recordings of those.

00:29:12.150 --> 00:29:13.552 align:middle line:84%
-Oh, you did?
-Yeah.

